# Environment Rules

## Security Requirements
- Store ALL sensitive data in .env file
- NEVER commit .env file to version control
- Create .env.example with placeholder values
- Validate environment variables at startup
- Use process.env for accessing variables

## Required Variables
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` - OpenAI API key (required)
- `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID` - Spotify client ID (optional)
- `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET` - Spotify client secret (optional)
- `NODE_ENV` - Environment (development/production)
- `PORT` - Server port (default: 3001)

## Configuration
- Centralize in `app/config/` directory
- Use environment variables for external services
- Implement validation on startup
- Provide clear error messages for missing config

```javascript
// Good: Environment validation
const openAIAPIKey = process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY;
if (!openAIAPIKey) {
  logWarn('OpenAI API key not set - AI features disabled');
}

// Bad: Hardcoded values
const apiKey = 'sk-1234567890abcdef';
```